NAME
    tree - list contents of directories in a tree-like format

SYNOPSIS
    tree [-d] [-L level] [path]

DESCRIPTION
    Displays the directory structure as a tree.
    Shows files and directories with visual connectors.

OPTIONS
    -d          List directories only
    -L level    Limit display to level depth

EXAMPLES
    tree
        Show tree from current directory

    tree /api
        Show tree from /api

    tree -L 2 /api/data
        Show 2 levels deep

    tree -d /
        Show only directories

OUTPUT
    /api
    ├── data/
    │   ├── users/
    │   └── orders/
    └── describe/

    2 directories, 0 files

SEE ALSO
    ls, find
